Edited page should trigger the [notification feature|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONF43/Managing+Notifications+in+Confluence] as well instead of just the following event:

{quote}
The workbox displays a notification when someone does one of the following in Confluence:

* [Shares|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONF43/Emailing+a+Page] a page or blog post with you.
* [Mentions|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONF43/Using+Mentions] you in a page, blog post or comment.
* Comments on a page or blog post that you are [watching|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONF43/Watching+a+Page+or+Blog+Post].
* [Likes|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONF43/Likes+and+Popular+Content] a page or blog post that you are watching.
The workbox does not show notifications triggered because you are watching a space. Only watches on pages and blog posts are relevant here.{quote}

By allowing page edition to be included into the notification feature, Confluence could discard e-mail notification altogether and rely on the notification feature.

*OR* administrator should be provided with the option to use the events that could trigger the notification feature

h2. Summary of The Bug

Confluence 4.2.4 installed with 2.7.2 resulting to the following ERROR:
{quote}
This version of Confluence is unknown to the plugin information server. It may be too new to appear, or it may be some type of non-standard build. No plugins can be found for unknown product versions.
{quote} 

!4.2.4upm.png|thumbnail!

Due the above error, Confluence was not able to search or check for new plugins.

h3. Workaround

# Access the following URL {{http://<server base url>/admin/viewplugins.action}}
# Uninstall Universal Plugin Manager
# Shutdown Confluence
# Remove the following directories
#* {{<confluence-home>/bundled-plugins}}
#* {{<confluence-home>/plugins-cache}}
#* {{<confluence-home>/plugins-osgi-cache}}
#* {{<confluence-home>/plugins-temp}}
# Restart Confluence

